<TITLE> UN's ICT chief to arrive Monday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 28 (bdnews24.com)The UN's ICT chief Hamadoun Tour is expected in Dhaka on Monday. Tour, secretary general of the International Telecommunications Union, the UN agency for information and communication technology affairs, will be in the country for a four-day visit. Post and telecommunications minister Rajiuddin Ahmed Raju will receive Tour at the airport on Monday afternoon, said the public relations office of the ministry. Tour is scheduled to attend the launching ceremony of a government initiative, 'Digital Bangladesh: Plan of Connecting People' during his visit. Prime minister Sheikh Hasina is expected to join the ceremony on Tuesday as chief guest. The International Telecommunication Union is the eldest organisation in the UN family still in existence. It was founded as the International Telegraph Union in 1865 before coming under the UN system. Since its formation, the ITU has coordinated the shared global use of the radio spectrum, promoted international cooperation in assigning satellite orbits, worked to improve telecommunication infrastructure in the developing world, established worldwide standards and addressed the global challenges of the time, such as strengthening cyber-security. The organisation is based in Geneva, Switzerland, and its membership includes 191 Member States.
